'''''Conus lignarius''''' is a [[species]] of sophisticated [[predatory]] sea [[snail]], a [[marine (ocean)|marine]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]], more popularly known as a [[cone snail]], cone shell or cone. 

Also see [[Cone snail]].

==Distribution==
This is an [[Indo-Pacific]] species. 

The [[biological type|type locality]] is Port Sacloban, [[Leyte (island)|Leyte Island]] in the Philippines.

